Rule: Description (In the case that the score is 50%...)
RuleCharNumber: 50% of the samples have more than 100 characters.
RuleWordNumber: 50% of the samples have between 20 and 100,000 words.
RuleSentenceNumber: 50% of the samples have between 3 and 7,500 sentences.
RuleLineEndWithTerminal: Over 60% of sentences in 50% of the samples end with terminal punctuation (.!?;).
RuleStopWord: Over 6% of words in 50% of the samples are stop words.
RuleAlphaWords: Over 60% of the words in 50% of the samples have alphabetic characters.
RuleMeanWordLength: 50% of the samples have a mean word length between 3 and 10 characters.
RuleCapitalWords: Over 20% of words in 50% of the samples are capitalised.
RuleLineEndWithEllipsis: Over 30% of sentences in 50% of the samples end with ellipsis (...).
RuleSpecialCharacter: 50% of the samples have special characters.
RuleLineStartWithBulletpoint: 50% of the samples start with a bullet point.
RuleDocRepeat: 50% of the samples have repeating lines.
RuleSymbolWordRatio: In 50% of the samples, the ratio between symbols and words is > 0.4.
RuleHtmlEntity: 50% of the samples have HTML content.
RuleUniqueWords: 50% of the samples have a ratio > 0.1 of unique words.
RuleCurlyBracket: There is a ratio > 0.1 between curly brackets and other characters in 50% of the samples.
RuleLoremIpsum: 50% of the samples contain Lorem Ipsum text.
RuleColonEnd: 50% of the samples finish in a colon (:).
RuleLineJavascriptCount: 50% of the samples contain the word "javascript".
